#Text=Aracaju
#Text=Aracaju is the capital of the state of Sergipe , Brazil .
#Text=It 's the capital of northeast with best quality of life ( according to Federal Government ) .
#Text=It 's located on the coast , and cut by rivers such as Sergipe and Poxim .
#Text=According to the population count conducted by the IBGE in 2007 , the city has 520,303 inhabitants . [ 1 ]
#Text=In addition to the populations of cities that form the Great Aracaju , Nossa Senhora do Socorro , Barra dos Coqueiros , Laranjeiras and São Cristóvão , number passes for 760,000 inhabitants .
#Text=The toponymy " Aracaju " derives from the expression indigenous " ará acaiú " , which in Tupi-guarani means " cashew of parrots " .

column1: #Text=The element " ará " means " Parrots " and " acaiú " , " fruit of the cashew . "
#Text=Get in
#Text=Bus and airplane connects with the whole country by São Paulo , Rio de Janeiro and other cities .
#Text=See
#Text=Aracaju Aquarium ( Oceanário de Aracaju ) , Atalaia .
#Text=5 fresh water tanks and 11 salt water tanks with fish from the coast of Sergipe .
#Text=Shark feeding at 4:30PM .
#Text=Aracaju Zoological Park .
#Text=Atalaia Shoreline ( Orla de Atalaia ) ( 9 kilometers from the city center ) .
#Text=Aracaju 's most famous beach area , 6 kilometers long , has the best concentration of hotels and restaurants .
#Text=Igreja de Santo Antônio .
#Text=Olímpio Campos Palace ( Palácio Olímpio Campos ) .
#Text=Museums
#Text=Anthropology Museum ( Museu de Antropologia ) .
#Text=Handcrafts Museum , Museu do Artesanato .
#Text=Museum of the Sergipana People ( Museu da Gente Sergipana ) .
#Text=Museum of the Sergipano Man ( Museu do Homem Sergipano ) .
#Text=Museum of the Sergipe Historical and Geographical Institute ( Museu do Instituto Histórico e Geográfico de Sergipe ) .
#Text=Rosa Faria Art and History Museum ( Museu de Arte e História Rosa Faria ) .
#Text=Sergipe Memorial Museum , Museu Memorial de Sergipe .
#Text=War Art Museum of the Sergipe Military Police ( Museu de Arte Bélica da Polícia Militar de Sergipe ) .
#Text=Do
#Text=The Atalaia beach was never highly rated for its natural beauty , but for an urban Brazilian beach it does the trick .
#Text=Plastic chairs in the sand for having beer and coconut are near Avenida Rotary .
#Text=A major refurbishing of the beachfront avenue , including its pavement , has made it a delightful walk at nighttime .
#Text=Apart from bars and restaurants by the dozens , there are a couple of clusters of bronze statues , a go-kart track , a large playground and an aquarium .
#Text=http://www.tamar.org.br/centros_visitantes.php?cod=10
#Text=Eat
#Text=Crabs are the typical dish , often eaten with a good and cold beer .
#Text=You also have good fishes , fried or cooked as moqueca .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=Most tourists will choose the beach at Atalaia , some 5 km from the center .

#Text=The most convenient spot for transport is the intersection between Avenida Rotary ( leading to the airport and downtown , with an urban bus terminal 500 metres from the beach ) and the beachfront Avenida Santos Dumont .
#Text=Plenty of options in the R$ 100-range within a couple of blocks here .
#Text=For more upscale sleeping , head north along the beach .
#Text=Go next
#Text=To the south , at the border with the state of Bahia , is Mangue Seco , an easy day trip .
#Text=Inland is the artificial lake of the river Xingo .
